~ inspector_intro
HydraBot: Great progress so far. Now let’s explore the inspector. [ID:D3A281_921842]
HydraBot: When you select a single device, take a look at the panel on the right. [ID:D3A281_45133C]

HydraBot: That’s the inspector. [ID:D3A281_70C87E]
HydraBot: It shows useful information like the device name, its MAC address, and the number of ports. [ID:D3A281_402E25]

HydraBot: If you select a switch, you’ll notice something interesting. [ID:D3A281_6FAC77]
HydraBot: It doesn’t have interaction options. [ID:D3A281_C183C5]

HydraBot: That’s because a switch doesn’t send messages like a computer does. [ID:D3A281_5AE1D1]
HydraBot: Instead, it quietly forwards data between devices. [ID:D3A281_F5315C]

HydraBot: Go ahead and click on different devices and observe how the inspector changes. [ID:D3A281_B367A0]

- Got it! [ID:D3A281_5D2E5B]
	HydraBot: Nice. Understanding your tools is key. [ID:D3A281_ED31B5]
	=> END
